ADP 1.1.1
Released: 2026-06-17
Source DNA: a multi-agent production system, ~80 deploy rounds
Spec: see the agentic-development-protocol repository (current/PROTOCOL.md)
Spec version: 1.1 (unchanged — 1.1.1 is an installer/tooling patch)

What's in 1.1 vs 1.0:
- Codebase-index skill (AST skeleton)
- Four skill archetypes with 3-level progressive disclosure
- Native Claude Code subagents + hooks + settings
- Model tiering defaults (Opus/Sonnet/Haiku)
- Attention-budget framing + two-layer memory
- Wire-format files (.adp/) — 5.3x compression for agent-to-agent state
- Dispatch freshness gate
- scripts/wire-sync.sh

What's new in 1.1.1 (installer & tooling — no spec change):
- init.sh merges hooks into an existing settings.json and appends .gitignore
  (no more silent SKIP that left enforcement inert)
- Prerequisite check (jq/bash/python3); --yes / non-TTY; --ci (CI is opt-in);
  --dry-run / --plan preview; warns before installing onto an uncommitted tree
- Enforcement-status output states the ACTUAL state (active / inert-no-jq /
  not-wired / prose-only) instead of a generic checklist
- Enforcement infra (.claude hooks + settings) ships only with --host=claude-code,
  so a generic install is truly prose-only
- INSTALL_MANIFEST written; uninstall.sh (safe / --dry-run / --purge)
- Cross-platform Node hooks (.mjs — no jq, no bash) + settings.node.json
- jq-less auto-wiring: with --host=claude-code on a host that has Node but no jq,
  init.sh now wires the Node hooks automatically (live enforcement, no manual step)
- verify-hooks.sh and verify-hooks.mjs offline self-tests
- PROJECT_NAME centralized to memory/CLAUDE.md (role prompts stay generic)
